Step 1: Determine Average Total Assets.  
 • Initial Total Assets = 13,000,000.00  
 • End Total Assets = 15,200,446.16  
 • Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 15,200,446.16) / 2  
  = 28,200,446.16 / 2  
  ≈ 14,100,223.08  

Step 2: Identify Total Revenue from the Income Statement.  
 • Main Business Revenue = 5,064,939.23  

Step 3: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.  
 • Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
  = 5,064,939.23 / 14,100,223.08  
  ≈ 0.3596  

Rounded to two decimals, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.36.

Thus, the final answer is:
